Defendant Demond L Thomas in court, in custody, with attorney Cameron Weitzner.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court strikes the repeater and finds defendant guilty.  Count #1 is dismissed and read in. 
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #2:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

150 DAYS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;(court would consider early termination of probation after 18 months); Probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling; 
*No violent contact with:   Victim, M.W.;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Domestic Violence Counseling;

COURT COSTS:  $343.00 (includes domestic abuse surcharge - to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 43 Days, apply 43 days, time served.
